<div class="prose">

<div class="callout">
  <div class="callout-title">📌 What "EAL" means here</div>
  EAL = English as an Additional Language. Material on this hub is for students whose strongest academic language is not English, their families, and teachers planning their support. None of this is gated — anyone is welcome to read it, but the Teacher Strategy Guide assumes a teacher audience and the Pre-Teach handouts assume a student audience.
</div>

<p>The course's grading model protects EAL students structurally. The <a href="/foundations/the-rubric/">AISC strand rubric</a> scores Knowledge &amp; Understanding (K/U), Thinking &amp; Transfer (T/T), and Communication (C) <strong>separately</strong>. Developing English does not drag down K/U or T/T. Strong science thinking in a second language receives the score it earns.</p>

</div>

